    "problemStatement": "Niven numbers are positive integers greater than 0 that are divisible by the sum of their digits. For\nexample, 42 is a Niven number, it is divisible by 4 + 2 = 6. You are given a function,\nint CheckNivenNumber(int n);\nint CheckNivenNumber(int n);\nstatic int CheckNivenNumber(int n);\nstatic int CheckNivenNumber(int n);\ndef CheckNivenNumber(n)\nThe function accepts an integer 'n' as its argument. Implement the function to check if 'n' is Niven.\nIf 'n' Niven, then return the number of times it is divisible by the sum of its digits (i.e. the quotient),\nelse return 0. Assume that 'n' > 0.",
